node.text: One of the weird gifts of my job is that sometimes they set you up with someone who your character falls in love with on screen and then you actually fall in love off screen. That was @satyasees (aka Shivrang to New Girl fam) and I. We were brother and sister in another life for realz. And we have maintained our off screen and on screen love affair… like in this amazing movie we did called Miss India America where he plays such a funny weird pageant MC. Spoiler alert: thankfully @taylorswift doesn’t scoop him up and run away with him half way through our scene. Love my brother from another mother. I also love wearing saris but that’s a whole other post. ❤️💙

I just want to share that as siblings who were raised in an Indian/ Greek household, for @ponderossa and I, quiet maturity was the cornerstone of the values that were taught in our house. Take life seriously. Don’t muck about. Don’t go in public and pull faces and embarrass the family. My brother and I hold those cultural values on high and make our parents proud in every moment.*

(*please disregard above photo)
(*if you have been in an Indian/ Greek household you will know that it is just a goofball house with the best food where loud means a good time and sarcasm is survival) 👫🏽🤪

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hannah Simone on July 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, child, sitting and indoor.

node.text: “Don’t meet artists you love.” When I worked at Much Music that was the mantra. The thinking was that if you met them and they were a jerk to you then you could never enjoy their music/ films/ shows the same way again. I remember thinking that was ludicrous. Are you going to tell me, a little girl who grew up in Cyprus and India and Saudi Arabia where there were no concerts or pop culture tv shows, where movies were censored, that I should now not sit down and talk to Beyoncé?! My thinking was okay maybe that artist does have a bad day and doesn’t want to answer my dumb questions okay so I see them and their normal human emotions from being at work all day. I can handle that moment and not define them by it. But also maybe I get this incredible opportunity to talk to someone whose art I absolutely love and get to deepen my understanding of it. Anywhoo this is me behind the scenes with icon @floriasigismondi and it was beyond the best experience ever. Anyone else meet someone whose work they admire and end up with a great story?💕
